---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'February 2026';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | BasisToolkit"
  description="Privacy Policy for basistoolkit.com — how this website handles data, cookies and third-party advertising."
  path="/privacy/"
>
  <section class="legal">
    <div class="wrap legal-wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how BasisToolkit ("we", "us", "the site") handles
        information when you visit <strong>basistoolkit.com</strong>. We keep this simple:
        the site is an information and download resource, and we collect as little as possible.
      </p>

      <h2>The desktop application</h2>
      <p>
        The SAP Logon Transfer application is a standalone desktop program that runs entirely
        on your own computer. It does <strong>not</strong> send your data to us or to any server.
        It only reads and writes your local SAP connection settings, and it never handles
        passwords. Nothing you do inside the application is transmitted to this website.
      </p>

      <h2>Information this website collects</h2>
      <p>
        We do not ask you to create an account, and we do not collect names, email addresses
        or other personal details through forms. Like most websites, our hosting provider may
        automatically log standard technical information — such as your browser type, device
        type, approximate region and the pages you visit — for security and to understand
        overall traffic. This information is aggregated and is not used to identify you.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and advertising</h2>
      <p>
        This site may display advertising, including through Google AdSense. Third-party
        vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this
        and other websites.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads to you
          based on your visit to this site and/or other sites on the Internet.
        </li>
        <li>
          You may opt out of personalised advertising by visiting
          <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          You can also opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalised
          advertising by visiting
          <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.aboutads.info</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Third-party vendors and ad networks may also use cookies to serve ads on this site.
        You can control cookies through your browser settings; disabling cookies will not
        prevent you from using the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We may use privacy-respecting analytics to understand which pages are useful. Any such
        analytics is used only in aggregate and does not identify individual visitors.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links</h2>
      <p>
        This site links to external sites (for example, SourceForge for downloads, and SAP's
        own documentation). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites;
        please review their policies separately.
      </p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This site is intended for IT professionals and is not directed at children under 13.
        We do not knowingly collect information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this
        page with a new "last updated" date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy can be directed through the
        <a href="/about/">About page</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="disclaimer muted">
        BasisToolkit is an independent project. It is not affiliated with, authorised by, or
        endorsed by SAP SE. "SAP" and other SAP product names are trademarks of SAP SE.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .legal-wrap { max-width: 760px; padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
    .legal h1 { font-size: var(--step-3); }
    .legal .updated { margin-top: -0.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    .legal h2 { font-size: var(--step-1); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
    .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--slate); line-height: 1.7; }
    .legal ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 0.8rem 0; }
    .legal .disclaimer { font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
